## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="d0c54-117">Cuando <xref:System.Runtime.InteropServices.SafeBuffer.AcquirePointer%2A> devuelve, se debe realizar vincula la comprobación, compruebe que la `pointer` parámetro es `null`.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="d0c54-117">When <xref:System.Runtime.InteropServices.SafeBuffer.AcquirePointer%2A> returns, you should perform bounds checking by verifying that the `pointer` parameter is `null`.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="d0c54-118">Si no lo es `null`, debe llamar a la <xref:System.Runtime.InteropServices.SafeBuffer.ReleasePointer%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> método en una región de ejecución restringida (CER).</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="d0c54-118">If it is not `null`, you must call the <xref:System.Runtime.InteropServices.SafeBuffer.ReleasePointer%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> method in a constrained execution region (CER).</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="d0c54-119"><xref:System.Runtime.InteropServices.SafeBuffer.AcquirePointer%2A> llamadas a la <xref:System.Runtime.InteropServices.SafeHandle.DangerousAddRef%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> método y expone el puntero.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="d0c54-119"><xref:System.Runtime.InteropServices.SafeBuffer.AcquirePointer%2A> calls the <xref:System.Runtime.InteropServices.SafeHandle.DangerousAddRef%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> method and exposes the pointer.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="d0c54-120">A diferencia de la <xref:System.Runtime.InteropServices.SafeBuffer.Read%2A> método, no cambia la posición actual del puntero.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="d0c54-120">Unlike the <xref:System.Runtime.InteropServices.SafeBuffer.Read%2A> method, it does not change the current position of the pointer.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="d0c54-121">El siguiente exampledemonstrates cómo utilizar el <xref:System.Runtime.InteropServices.SafeBuffer.AcquirePointer%2A> método:</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="d0c54-121">The following exampledemonstrates how to use the <xref:System.Runtime.InteropServices.SafeBuffer.AcquirePointer%2A> method:</span></span>  
  
```  
byte* pointer = null;  
RuntimeHelpers.PrepareConstrainedRegions();  
try {  
    MySafeBuffer.AcquirePointer(ref pointer);  
    // Use pointer here, with your own bounds checking.  
    }  
finally {  
    if (pointer != null)  
        MySafeBuffer.ReleasePointer();  
    }  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="d0c54-122">Si convierte `pointer` (que es un puntero a un byte) como un puntero a un tipo diferente (T \*), puede tener problemas de alineación de puntero.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="d0c54-122">If you cast `pointer` (which is a pointer to a byte) as a pointer to a different type (T\*), you may have pointer alignment issues.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="d0c54-123">Debe asumir la responsabilidad de comprobación con this (puntero) de todos los límites.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="d0c54-123">You must take responsibility for all bounds checking with this pointer.</span></span>

